LG.L:
I set here aue [sic in MS. Read ane] þat may be sayde; 

I set here ane that may be sayd

If thu of ane and be vnpurwayde.—D.

Þe awter, and sithen turne hym aboute; 

After þo weschyng þo pryst wyl lowte

Þo awter kyste and storne hym a-bowte.—A.

If þou be vnpuruayde;
I set here ane that may be sayd
If thu of ane and be vnpurwayde.—D. Prayer to Christ present in form of bread.

Sethen dres ðam [MS. dresdam] in þe firste stede; 

He wyll sprede his armes o-brade

Sethen dresse thaim in thaier friste stede.—D.

ȝef of oyn thu be vn-purueyd; 

I set here ane that may be sayd

If thu of ane and be vnpurwayde.—D.
